		<div class="courseListDescription">This course builds on the material in AFF 310. Financial options and their applications in risk management are further explored. Students examine treasury management, liquidity and short term finance. Various valuation approaches and models are examined in detail. Methodologies for applying valuation models to complex issues are discussed. EXCEL skills introduced in AFF 210 and AFF 310 are extended and reinforced.</div>
	
	
